## When to use
When you need a quick way to check the current status of your disk space from the command line without typing out the full `df -h` command each time.

## Approach
Create a custom shell function in your `.bashrc` or similar file that executes the `shell_exec` tool with the argument 'df -h' to display human-readable disk usage information.

## Example
```shell
function quick_disk_status {
  shell_exec "df -h"
}
```

## Pitfalls
Ensure you source your .bashrc file after adding the function or log out and back in again so that the new function is recognized.